Load The Data to Staging Table and populate it

Step 1: Drag and drop the OLEDB Destination  transformation to the control flow.

Step 2: Double click on OLEDB  Destination and select OLEDB connection manager and select the staging table.

Step 3: Map the columns.

Step 4: Click on Execute or Start button top to run the package. This will load the staging table.



A staging area or landing zone, is an intermediate storage area used for data processing during the extract, transform and load (ETL) process. Please click on the link below for more information.

What is staging table?
